abstract: Stocks end modestly higher as investors ignore concerns about tensions in Middle East and dip in consumer confidence.
lead_paragraph: Energy stocks rose, but shares of airlines and travel companies sank as investors feared a drop in travel and vacation spending.

headline.main: Wall St. Ticks Upward, Shaking Off Fears on Middle East
headline.print_headline: Investors Shake Off Early Concerns About the Middle East and Consumers
